Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the wedges cook, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #cutting board{}. Cut into 1cm chunks.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams}, sliced pepper and onion and stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then stir in the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add in the black beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @soured cream{75%grams} and lime zest.

When the fajita mix is ready, squeeze in some lime juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your plates and top with the chorizo fajita mix.

Top with the avocado and scatter over the cheese. Finish with a big dollop of the zesty soured cream - wedges loaded!

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!